The paper deals with motion planning for autonomous ground robots, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of neural networks for learning the mapping from perception to decision suggests that the paper may also fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of 2D-laser range findings and target positions suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) may also be relevant. Finally, the fact that the model is able to navigate in real-world environments suggests that the paper may also fall under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
